    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - LIFT AXLE SYSTEMS - SPECIFICATIONS - TORQUE SETTINGS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl14019082" svcproctype="torque" graphiccount="2">
        <title>TORQUE SETTINGS</title>
        <para>The fasteners listed in
            <hotlnk xrefid="t14019m">TABLE 21</hotlnk>, and indicated in
            <hotlnk xrefid="f14019bs">FIGURE 52</hotlnk>, have unique or critical torque settings. Torque values for the
            U-bolts used on the fixed lift axles are listed in
            <hotlnk xrefid="t14019e">TABLE 22</hotlnk>. Torque values for the general fasteners are listed in
            <hotlnk xrefid="t14019f">TABLE 23</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <para>When the vehicle is first placed into service, the fasteners should be retorqued at the following
            intervals:
        </para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>after the first 5 days of service,</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>after the first 30 days of service,</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>after the first 60 days of service,</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>every 6 months thereafter.</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
